The Oasis-Pyramid Corridor is the logistical arc connecting desert roads, cistern law, and oasis administration to the three pyramids.
The oases were not passive waystations but the administrative infrastructure that made the pyramids possible.

The Deepwell Confluence is a single deep limestone aquifer. Three fracture networks produce three oases.
Great Oasis: primary vent, largest and most reliable. Northern Oasis: tertiary fracture, weakest and most brackish. Southern Oasis: secondary fracture, mid-size.
The vanished Iseth Reach river once fed the entire system. When it dried, all hydraulic connections were severed simultaneously.

Three pyramids represent three responses to the Black Sun Shard:
  Great Pyramid - contain it through institutional precision.
  Northern Pyramid - guard the container with military force.
  Southern Pyramid - descend toward its source and understand it.

The Twin Sovereign Schism divided the corridor. Sand Sovereign: authority flows from celestial order down. Moon Sovereign: authority flows from underworld death forces up.
Northern Oasis aligned with measurement and transparency. Southern Oasis aligned with survival and acceptance of death.

The Ninth Meridian Rite, a last attempt to reconcile solar and underworld doctrines, failed because the two systems were cosmologically incompatible.
The oases are the logistical foundation without which no pyramid could have been built, staffed, or supplied.
